{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566757","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566757"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:47:46+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:47:46+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18874"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18874","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18874"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.95,0.01,0.01,0.01,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11607"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80149"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11607","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11607"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18874"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65426"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"5335"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5644"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11323"},{"type":"tags","id":"11326"},{"type":"tags","id":"11327"},{"type":"tags","id":"11328"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27315"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27387"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80149","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80149"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EHealthcare professionals need to maintain a healthy work-life balance to prevent burnout and maintain wellbeing while working in demanding clinical environments.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes an effective strategy for maintaining work-life balance?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Checking work emails only during designated times","Working through lunch breaks to finish daily tasks on time","Taking work projects home to decrease office hours","Skipping breaks to leave early","Accepting all overtime requests to reduce financial stress"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe effective strategy is \u003Cstrong\u003Echecking work emails only during designated times\u003C/strong\u003E. This approach helps maintain clear professional boundaries while ensuring work responsibilities are met in a structured way that prevents burnout. Setting specific times for email checking reduces stress and prevents work from encroaching on personal time.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe ineffective strategies are:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWorking through lunch breaks to finish daily tasks on time\u003C/strong\u003E - Regular breaks are essential for maintaining focus, preventing fatigue, and allowing time for rest and nutrition. Research shows that taking breaks improves overall productivity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETaking work projects home to decrease office hours\u003C/strong\u003E - This blurs work-life boundaries and can lead to overwork, chronic stress, and reduced quality of personal time. Home should be preserved as a space for rest and recovery.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESkipping breaks to leave early\u003C/strong\u003E - Regular breaks are necessary for maintaining productivity, cognitive function, and physical wellbeing. Continuous work without breaks leads to decreased performance and increased error rates.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAccepting all overtime requests to reduced financial stress\u003C/strong\u003E- Setting appropriate limits on work hours is essential for preventing burnout. Excessive overtime is associated with increased medical errors and poorer mental health outcomes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EResearch shows that healthcare professionals who maintain clear work-life boundaries and engage in regular self-care activities report lower burnout rates, higher job satisfaction, and provide better quality patient care. Establishing routines and boundaries around work communications is a key component of sustainable professional practice.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Regular physical activity improves cognitive function, mental health, and work performance.","Work-life balance strategies that include exercise help prevent burnout in healthcare professionals.","Effective work-life balance requires setting boundaries and maintaining regular routines."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx.","Bodendieck E, Jung FU, Conrad I, Riedel-Heller SG, Hussenoeder FS. The work-life balance of general practitioners as a predictor of burnout and motivation to stay in the profession. BMC Primary Care. 2022;23(1):218. Available at: https://bmcprimcare.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12875-022-01831-7"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65426"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18874"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65426","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65426"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-17T20:24:41+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-17T20:28:01+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11607"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80149"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"sel